<subSubSection id="C35B53C89E75FFB1B7E7FF45FB1F6FB9" pageId="2" pageNumber="401" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BFE00439E75FFB1B7E7FF45FABD6FE1" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E75FFB1B7E7FF45FE106EFC" authorityName="Napp &amp; Martins" authorityYear="1985" box="[151,385,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Gnomidolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="401" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incisum">
<emphasis id="B935DC519E75FFB1B7E7FF45FE106EFC" box="[151,385,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">Gnomidolon incisum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<materialsCitation id="3B290A1E9E75FFB1B6F8FF45FAB66FE1" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3766135306" country="Venezuela" location="We" municipality="This" pageId="2" pageNumber="401" specimenCount="6" typeStatus="paratype">
is known only from its type-locality in 
<collectingCountry id="F35640D39E75FFB1B44BFF45FC3F6EFD" box="[827,942,151,177]" name="Venezuela" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD07DB29E75FFB1B4CDFF45FB296EFD" author="Napp, D. S. &amp; Martins, U. R." box="[957,1208,150,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="401" pagination="111 - 130" refId="ref12306" refString="Napp, D. S. &amp; Martins, U. R. (1985) Ibidionini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae) Ia. Divisao: notas, chaves e descricoes. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 36 (12), 111 - 130." type="journal article" year="1985">Napp &amp; Martins 1985</bibRefCitation>
). 
<location id="8E9E56989E75FFB1B3BBFF45FB616EFD" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E8B1559E76FFB1B7E7FC11FB1F6FB9:8E9E56989E75FFB1B3BBFF45FB616EFD" box="[1227,1264,151,177]" country="Venezuela" municipality="This" name="We" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">We</location>
examined a female specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F35640D39E75FFB1B60FFF69FDF76E99" box="[383,614,187,213]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">Trinidad and Tobago</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="137A1CC69E75FFB1B504FF69FD256E99" box="[628,692,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1141,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-225@1.[151,1436,1141,1919]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Gnomidolon incisum Napp &amp; Martins, 1985. 1) Female from Trinidad and Tobago, dorsal habitus. 2) Paratype from Venezuela, dorsal habitus. 3–4) Female from Trinidad and Tobago, apex of metafemur: 3) Left metafemur; 4) Right metafemur. 5) Paratype from Venezuela, apex of left metafemur." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538415" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538415/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingMunicipality id="6B9A9A399E75FFB1B5BBFF69FD6C6E99" box="[715,765,187,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">This</collectingMunicipality>
specimen differs from the type material (
<typeStatus id="54FABEE19E75FFB1B3B4FF69FAB76E99" box="[1220,1318,187,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">paratype</typeStatus>
illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="137A1CC69E75FFB1B7C5FF0DFF686EB5" box="[181,249,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1141,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-225@1.[151,1436,1141,1919]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Gnomidolon incisum Napp &amp; Martins, 1985. 1) Female from Trinidad and Tobago, dorsal habitus. 2) Paratype from Venezuela, dorsal habitus. 3–4) Female from Trinidad and Tobago, apex of metafemur: 3) Left metafemur; 4) Right metafemur. 5) Paratype from Venezuela, apex of left metafemur." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538415" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538415/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) by the scape orangish (dark reddish brown in the 
<typeStatus id="54FABEE19E75FFB1B430FF0DFC336EB5" box="[832,930,223,249]" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="54FABEE19E75FFB1B4ABFF0DFBD16EB5" box="[987,1088,223,249]" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">paratype</typeStatus>
), and elytra without dark band projected toward anterior third along suture (present in the 
<typeStatus id="54FABEE19E75FFB1B444FED1FC076F51" box="[820,918,259,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="54FABEE19E75FFB1B4BEFED1FBA56F51" box="[974,1076,259,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">paratype</typeStatus>
). As there are no morphological structures differentiating the specimens, we concluded these are just chromatic variations. The length of the inner spine of the left metafemur is considerably different in the specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F35640D39E75FFB1B4A0FE99FB286F29" box="[976,1209,331,357]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">Trinidad and Tobago</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="137A1CC69E75FFB1B3B7FE99FA9B6F29" box="[1223,1290,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1141,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-225@1.[151,1436,1141,1919]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Gnomidolon incisum Napp &amp; Martins, 1985. 1) Female from Trinidad and Tobago, dorsal habitus. 2) Paratype from Venezuela, dorsal habitus. 3–4) Female from Trinidad and Tobago, apex of metafemur: 3) Left metafemur; 4) Right metafemur. 5) Paratype from Venezuela, apex of left metafemur." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538415" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538415/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); however, it varies within the same specimen and, in fact, the length of the inner spine of the right metafemur (
<figureCitation id="137A1CC69E75FFB1B3BEFEBDFA816FC5" box="[1230,1296,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1141,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-225@1.[151,1436,1141,1919]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Gnomidolon incisum Napp &amp; Martins, 1985. 1) Female from Trinidad and Tobago, dorsal habitus. 2) Paratype from Venezuela, dorsal habitus. 3–4) Female from Trinidad and Tobago, apex of metafemur: 3) Left metafemur; 4) Right metafemur. 5) Paratype from Venezuela, apex of left metafemur." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538415" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538415/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) agrees well with that in the 
<typeStatus id="54FABEE19E75FFB1B637FE41FE366FE1" box="[327,423,403,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="401">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E75FFB1B6BDFE41FDD76FE0" authorityName="Napp &amp; Martins" authorityYear="1985" box="[461,582,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Gnomidolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="401" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incisum">
